HEADWORD: heaps
<hw>heaps</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a large quantity. See <er>heap</er>,
senses 2 and 3; <as>as, he made <ex>heaps</ex> of money in the stock
market</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tons, dozens, lots, piles, scores, stacks, loads,
rafts, slews, wads, oodles, gobs, scads, lashings.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

